<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-444-545  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 444 545.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 21 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mead Data Central opens new libraries on war and peace.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mead Corp. Mead Data Central (information services).andO;Topic:     NEXIS (Information retrieval system)Single European marketKuwaitIraqData Bases.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MEAD DATA CENTRAL OPENS NEW LIBRARIES ON WAR AND PEACE DAYTON, OHIO, U.S.A.,andO;1990 AUG 21 (NB) -- Mead Data Central has opened two new files on its Nexisservice, one covering war and the other peace.andM;The war file is a special collection of data on the Iraqi takeover of Kuwaitand its aftermath.andP;  The IRAQWR file is updated every 24 hours and includesdocuments from 22 publications and other sources including The WashingtonPost, Chicago Tribune, and TASS.andP;  Searching the file costs $21.andM;The pace file is called EUROPE NEWS and covers issues relating to the unifiedCommon Market due to take effect in 1992.andP;  It was built using the Term-BasedTopic Identification program developed by Mead, using natural languageprocessing principles to make sure that articles found in a search are trulyrelevant.andP;  Sources include The Times of London, Business Week, The Economist,and company information from EXTEL Cards and Europescope, a weekly file fromCoopers andamp; Lybrand.andP;  Prices range from $6-32 per search, depending on thenature of data sought, with corporate and legal files having the highestprices, news stories the lowest.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900821/Press Conact: Michelle Love, Mead Data Central,513-865-7466)</TEXT></DOC>